Sector B (KG) / kitchen
Astrea of the Stars 14-Aug-21 07:12 PM
WARNING: THIS PLACE IS LOCKED AT NIGHT TIME. A standard kitchen, all things considered. Are you happy? The kitchen itself is pretty unremarkable - it's definitely not here for decoration. The metal walls here are a bit lighter than the walls in the cafeteria, but not by much. The lights in here are bright, but are sterile and feel like they have no 'soul' to them. This room... feels like it just exists. Multiple sinks line up the place, alongside many, many places to cook. Pots and pans line up the room, but so do knives (though they just seem to be typical kitchen knives, honestly). There's veggies and other basic ingredients in the closet here, though some are in a huge freezer to keep them fresh. Everything you possibly could imagine being needed to cook something is here in some way, shape, or form, though it's up to your OC to actually be able to use everything here. There's also some basic cleaning supplies to clean off the counters and the floor, though of course you can use them for other purposes. Why is it so unremarkable, though? You feel like it should have more things in it. But no... it's simply a plain place. (edited)
